          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Start by telling one trusted person the truth: I am struggling and I need help. That is the first step. It is vulnerability, not weakness. Then tell them specifically what you need. Do not expect them to guess. Say: I need you to check on me every week. Or: I need you to tell me if you see me drifting. Or: I committed to this goal and I need you to hold me to it. Make it concrete. Then give them permission to speak up without you getting defensive. That is the contract of real accountability."
